            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Worst experience had been there for my child admission, all the staff members were very rude they have so much of attitude and the principal was the worst don’t know how to talk to parents all he was asking irrelevant personal questions and after making the registration they said the seats are full but got to know the real reason ,that they want that the child taking admission there should have both of there parents well educated and qualified and they should not belong to some local place or village\nWorst experience ever",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Modern Delhi International School - Sector 87"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Bhavika"
          },
          "datePublished": "2026-03-25",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "My experience with Modern Delhi International School was absolutely disgraceful and deeply upsetting. From the moment we arrived, we were treated with a shocking lack of respect and basic courtesy. We were made to wait unnecessarily for a long time with no proper communication, which already showed how little they value parents and students.\nWhat is even more disturbing is the clear bias and discriminatory attitude we faced. It genuinely felt like we were judged and denied admission because we belong to the Gujjar community and come from a village background. This kind of behavior is not just unprofessional—it is completely unacceptable in any educational institution.\nSchools are supposed to promote equality, dignity, and opportunity for all. Instead, this school appears to practice exclusion and prejudice behind closed doors. Such mindset has no place in modern education.\nI strongly condemn this kind of treatment and urge the authorities to seriously investigate their admission practices and staff behavior. No student or family should ever have to go through such humiliation. If this is how they treat people at the admission stage, it raises serious questions about the values they are instilling in their students.\nHighly disappointed and would not recommend this institution to anyone who expects fairness, respect, and basic human decency.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
